# License Information for openDesk Edu

openDesk Edu uses a **dual licensing model**.

## Orchestration Layer — AGPL-3.0-or-later

The orchestration layer — including helmfiles, deployment scripts,
automation, CI/CD pipelines, test infrastructure, and build configurations
in `helmfile/`, `scripts/`, `dev/`, `tests/`, `.ralph/`, `.gitlab/`, `.github/`,
`Makefile`, and `ct.yaml` — is licensed under the **GNU Affero General
Public License v3.0 or later**. See `LICENSES/AGPL-3.0-or-later.txt`.

This prevents proprietary SaaS capture of the platform while allowing
universities and public administrations to deploy, modify, and operate freely.

## Specifications, Documentation, and Content — Apache-2.0

The specifications, documentation, and content — including OpenSpec specs
(`openspec/`, `opendesk-edu-spec/`), articles, papers, and documentation
(`articles/`, `papers/`, `docs/`) — is licensed under the **Apache License,
Version 2.0**. See `LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt`.

This ensures specifications and knowledge can be freely adopted, adapted,
and shared without legal friction.

## Upstream Components

openDesk Edu integrates many independent open-source projects, each with
its own license. Individual services carry their own licenses (AGPL-3.0
for Nextcloud/Element, Apache-2.0 for openDesk CE, MIT for various libs).
This file covers only the openDesk Edu orchestration and integration layer.

## Contributions

By contributing, you agree that orchestration contributions are
AGPL-3.0-or-later, and spec/doc/content contributions are Apache-2.0.
